Selenium WebDriver works using a client-server architecture. The test script sends commands through the Selenium client library 
to the browser driver such as ChromeDriver. The browser driver communicates with the real browser
and performs the required actions, then sends the response back to the test script.

Test Script
     ↓
Selenium Client Library
     ↓
Browser Driver
     ↓
Real Browser
     ↓
Response Back
